Dresser Industries Inc said the U.S.Court of Appeals ruled against it in its appeal of a 1985judgment in favor of Hughes Tool Co &lt;HT> concerning a patentinfringement.    The case alleged that Dresser infringed on a Hughes patentregarding a drill bit sealing device, the company said.    However, Dresser said the Appellate Court set aside theroyalty rate of 25 pct on selected bits as being arbitarary andreturned the case to the district court level to ascertain anew rate. Reuter&#3;